FIRST(A) = FIRST(cS | epsilon) = {c, epsilon}
FIRST(B) = FIRST(epsilon) = {epsilon}

FIRST(AaAb): A can derive epsilon, so:
  = (FIRST(A) - {epsilon}) union FIRST(a...) = {c} union {a} = {a, c}

FIRST(BbBa): B can derive epsilon, so:
  = (FIRST(B) - {epsilon}) union FIRST(b...) = {} union {b} = {b}

So for S:
  S->AaAb is triggered by {a, c}
  S->BbBa is triggered by {b}
